FT  03 JUN 92 / Opposition to air union merger
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A CONTROVERSIAL plan for Cabin Crew 89, the airline workers' union, to join
the electrical section of the AEEU craft union seems doomed to failure after
strong opposition from AEEU engineering leaders.
Leaders of the engineering section yesterday told their colleagues who head
the electrical section that an amalgamation with Cabin Crew could not happen
because of opposition from the TUC.
