<HEADLINE>
FT  03 JUN 92 / US 'abusing Mexican migrants'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAMIAN FRASER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MEXICO CITY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
US immigration authorities routinely beat and abuse undocumented Mexican
migrants and occasionally shoot, torture and sexually abuse them, claims
Americas Watch, the human rights organisation, writes Damian Fraser in
Mexico City.
When complaints are filed, the US government is as 'defensive and
unyielding' as countries with poor human rights records, the group says.
Its report documents the case of one officer who, during a six to seven-year
period was involved in theft, two 'vehicle incidents,' one of which resulted
in the death of a migrant, two serious assaults on farm workers, and the
violent homicide of a Mexican minor.
The agent still works for border control.
</TEXT>
