FT  02 JUN 92 / Discussion on aid for Names
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE COUNCIL of the Lloyd's of London insurance market will consider a
proposal to help some of the worst-affected Names at its monthly meeting
tomorrow.
However, Lloyd's said yesterday that there was no certainty that it would
adopt any plan. An ad hoc committee has been considering possible schemes
for several weeks. The adoption of any plan is likely to depend on the
approval in a ballot of the market's 22,400 Names - wealthy individuals
whose capital backs the market.
The Names may have to meet much of the cost of any scheme through a special
levy. Although most agencies - which manage syndicates and handle the
affairs of Names - favour a bail-out plan, many of the Names are less
enthusiastic.
