<HEADLINE>
FT  02 JUN 92 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
There were 17,760 packages for the day, reports the Tea Brokers'
Association. The Landed market continued selective. Good liquoring east
Africans ruled firm to dearer with dusts a better feature, but mediums were
2-3p lower and some plainer lines were neglected. Central Africans also
tended easier. Offshore teas came in for limited support and prices were
generally easier for all descriptions. The highest price realised this week
was 201p for a Rwanda pd. Quotations: quality: 155p, good medium: 132p,
medium: 103p, low medium: 86p.
</TEXT>
