<HEADLINE>
FT  02 JUN 92 / International Capital Markets: UBS calls in Mountleigh bond
after payment missed
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ZURICH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
UNION Bank of Switzerland has called in the Mountleigh Finance 5 1/4 per
cent SFr150m 1988-1995 bond, Reuter reports from Zurich.
UBS said it had acted as neither the issuer nor the guarantor - collapsed UK
property company Mountleigh Group - had made an interest payment due on the
bonds on May 19.
Last month, UBS had announced that Mountleigh had a 10-day grace period to
meet the payment, and this too had now elapsed. Mountleigh collapsed when
banks owed some Pounds 400m withdrew support and put in KPMG Peat Marwick as
receivers.
Last week, Geneva-based Warburg Soditic also declared three Mountleigh Swiss
franc bonds, for which it acted as lead-manager, as due and payable.
