<HEADLINE>
FT  02 JUN 92 / The Lex Column: US economy
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
So far it looks as though the strong personal income/consumer spending
patterns and weak output/employment trends which marked the first quarter in
the US will be reversed in the second three months. While yesterday's jump
in the widely watched US purchasing managers' index for May to some extent
merely makes up ground lost in April, the advance is nevertheless consistent
with a relatively robust manufacturing recovery. It also suggests that the
US is well ahead of the UK at this stage in the cycle. All six components
showed good gains, with the employment number bolstering hopes that Friday's
eagerly awaited official May job statistics will show an improvement.
</TEXT>
