<DATELINE>
   CANBERRA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Australian government is considering merging Qantas Airways, the
state-owned international carrier, with Australian Airlines, the
government's domestic airline, and might then sell part of the merged group,
AP-DJ reports from Canberra.
Prime Minister Mr Paul Keating said in a television interview yesterday that
the proposal would be considered by the cabinet today and tomorrow. He added
that the government might sell 70 per cent of the merged airline in an
initial public offering, with international airlines allowed to acquire
holdings.
The government previously announced plans to sell all of Australian Airlines
and 49 per cent of Qantas.
