   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CBS will charge affiliate stations to carry certain programmes, a plan which
would radically alter the way the US television network deals with its
affiliates, a New York newspaper reported yesterday, Reuter reports from New
York.
The network said the change was needed because of low profits and increased
competition from the Fox and cable networks and programme syndicators.
