FT  01 JUN 92 / Indonesia opposition in show of strength
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   JAKARTA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
INDONESIA'S populist opposition party, campaigning against government
corruption and press censorship, claimed a street turnout of 3m supporters
yesterday - the last campaign day in the capital before the June 9 election,
Reuter reports from Jakarta. This is the biggest street demonstration since
general election campaigning started three weeks ago.
'The biggest enemy is corruption not inflation,' leaders of the Indonesian
Democratic party (PDI) told a big crowd in Jakarta. They said police
reported that 3m PDI supporters had gone into the streets, dwarfing
Saturday's estimated 1m people campaigning for the ruling Golkar party.
